{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014uLDnS6TJG2gXHAE6FQgw2","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I now have all the information I need. Let me compile the findings:\n\n## Summary\n\nI've found how the workflow view handles step content display. Here are the key components:\n\n### 1. **API Endpoint for Step Content** \n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n**Lines:** 1134-1199\n\nThe `handleAPIStepContent` function serves step content at the endpoint:\n```\nGET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content\n```\n\n**Key behavior (lines 1177-1196):**\n- Reads referenced files from disk based on step configuration\n- For `prompt` config: reads the file at the path specified (line 1177-1182)\n- For `command` config: returns the command string directly (line 1184-1186)\n- For `script` config: reads the file at the path, or returns the string if file not found (line 1188-1196)\n- **File contents ARE being read** - it uses `os.ReadFile()` to fetch actual content\n\n### 2. **Frontend Step Click Handler**\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`\n**Lines:** 251-284\n\nThe `openDrawer()` function handles clicking on workflow DAG nodes:\n- Line 233: Step nodes are clickable with `onclick=\"openDrawer('workflowName','stepName')\"`\n- Line 274: Fetches content from the API endpoint above\n- Line 275-282: Displays the content in a drawer panel, with HTML escaping for safety\n\n### 3. **Step Output Handler (Run Detail View)**\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n**Lines:** 563-634\n\nThe `handleAPIStepOutput` function serves execution output at:\n```\nGET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output\n```\n\n**Key behavior:**\n- Tries log index first (lines 575-591)\n- Falls back to file path conventions (lines 596-622)\n- Reads actual log file contents and returns them\n- **File contents ARE being read** - multiple `os.ReadFile()` calls\n\n### 4. **Frontend Step Output Toggle**\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html`\n**Lines:** 212-236\n\nClicking on a step row toggles the output display:\n- Line 225: Fetches `/api/runs/{runId}/steps/{step}/output`\n- Line 230: Displays the text content in a `<pre>` element\n\n### File Paths Summary\n\n1. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Main handler logic\n2. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - Workflow view with step drawer\n3. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - Run detail view with step output toggle\n4. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` - Styling (CSS variables only, no logic)\n\n**Conclusion:** File contents ARE actually being read from disk and served to the frontend via the API endpoints. The system doesn't just return filenames - it reads and returns the full content."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a7c6bf60731ba4ff5 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 41604\ntool_uses: 9\nduration_ms: 18542</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"568632a5-c6f9-4716-acd6-dad26849e95f","uuid":"0a12fb36-4bb4-495a-bd8c-faeab787c92f","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand how the workflow view handles step content display. Look at:\n\n1. internal/adapters/web/handler.go - find any handler related to step content, steps, or workflow view\n2. All files in internal/adapters/web/static/ - especially JavaScript files\n3. Any templates in internal/adapters/web/ \n\nFocus on:\n- How step clicks are handled in the frontend\n- What API endpoint serves step content\n- Whether file contents are actually being read or just filenames returned\n\nGive me the relevant code sections with file paths and line numbers.","agentId":"a7c6bf60731ba4ff5","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I now have all the information I need. Let me compile the findings:\n\n## Summary\n\nI've found how the workflow view handles step content display. Here are the key components:\n\n### 1. **API Endpoint for Step Content** \n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n**Lines:** 1134-1199\n\nThe `handleAPIStepContent` function serves step content at the endpoint:\n```\nGET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content\n```\n\n**Key behavior (lines 1177-1196):**\n- Reads referenced files from disk based on step configuration\n- For `prompt` config: reads the file at the path specified (line 1177-1182)\n- For `command` config: returns the command string directly (line 1184-1186)\n- For `script` config: reads the file at the path, or returns the string if file not found (line 1188-1196)\n- **File contents ARE being read** - it uses `os.ReadFile()` to fetch actual content\n\n### 2. **Frontend Step Click Handler**\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`\n**Lines:** 251-284\n\nThe `openDrawer()` function handles clicking on workflow DAG nodes:\n- Line 233: Step nodes are clickable with `onclick=\"openDrawer('workflowName','stepName')\"`\n- Line 274: Fetches content from the API endpoint above\n- Line 275-282: Displays the content in a drawer panel, with HTML escaping for safety\n\n### 3. **Step Output Handler (Run Detail View)**\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n**Lines:** 563-634\n\nThe `handleAPIStepOutput` function serves execution output at:\n```\nGET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output\n```\n\n**Key behavior:**\n- Tries log index first (lines 575-591)\n- Falls back to file path conventions (lines 596-622)\n- Reads actual log file contents and returns them\n- **File contents ARE being read** - multiple `os.ReadFile()` calls\n\n### 4. **Frontend Step Output Toggle**\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html`\n**Lines:** 212-236\n\nClicking on a step row toggles the output display:\n- Line 225: Fetches `/api/runs/{runId}/steps/{step}/output`\n- Line 230: Displays the text content in a `<pre>` element\n\n### File Paths Summary\n\n1. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Main handler logic\n2. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - Workflow view with step drawer\n3. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - Run detail view with step output toggle\n4. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` - Styling (CSS variables only, no logic)\n\n**Conclusion:** File contents ARE actually being read from disk and served to the frontend via the API endpoints. The system doesn't just return filenames - it reads and returns the full content."}],"totalDurationMs":18542,"totalTokens":41604,"totalToolUseCount":9,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4050,"cache_read_input_tokens":36786,"output_tokens":761,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4050},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
